WEBVTT

00:11.971 --> 00:13.389
[Ray]
Previously on  Ray Donovan...

00:13.389 --> 00:15.100
[grunting, gunshot]

00:15.100 --> 00:16.059
[panting]

00:16.059 --> 00:16.976
[gunshot]

00:19.353 --> 00:20.771
[Ray]
He's with the Russian mob.

00:20.771 --> 00:22.273
What does that have
to do with us?

00:22.273 --> 00:24.109
[Ray]
Mickey got in over his head

00:24.109 --> 00:25.776
with an Armenian family
in Glendale.

00:25.776 --> 00:28.904
Snitched to the police
to protect himself.

00:28.904 --> 00:30.448
Snitched on who?

00:30.448 --> 00:32.242
[Ray]
First the Armenians,

00:32.242 --> 00:33.909
then a Russian
they were in business with.

00:33.909 --> 00:36.120
So we decided
to go after him ourselves.

00:36.120 --> 00:37.455
It's not just art,
is it?

00:37.455 --> 00:39.206
It's drugs, girls.

00:39.206 --> 00:41.208
Belikov runs
your whole operation.

00:41.208 --> 00:44.295
What do I got to do
to make this go away?

00:44.295 --> 00:48.215
speaking Russian

00:48.215 --> 00:50.426
[yelling]

00:50.426 --> 00:53.263
I got a sure thing happening,
and I could use a partner.

00:53.263 --> 00:55.098
Back in Primm,
inside a casino,

00:55.098 --> 00:56.682
there's a gorgeous
green horseshoe

00:56.682 --> 00:58.434
filled with four million
in cash.

00:58.434 --> 01:00.186
No one's even watching it.

01:00.186 --> 01:02.188
Tomorrow night
in the middle of the party,

01:02.188 --> 01:03.230
we cut the power.

01:03.230 --> 01:05.108
We grab the horseshoe,

01:05.108 --> 01:06.817
and we're out
before anyone is the wiser.

01:06.817 --> 01:09.069
[tires squealing]

01:09.069 --> 01:11.197
I had a mammogram, Ray.

01:11.197 --> 01:14.242
It's something called
stage zero breast cancer.

01:14.242 --> 01:16.244
Please.
I can deliver a child.

01:16.244 --> 01:18.163
Get the fuck out
of our way, asshole!

01:18.163 --> 01:19.497
Hands! Hands!

01:19.497 --> 01:22.041
Put the fucking gun down.
Put it down.

01:22.041 --> 01:23.709
She keeps fucking texting me,

01:23.709 --> 01:25.127
threatening to kill me.

01:25.127 --> 01:26.962
There's a  puta
that I been fuckin'.

01:26.962 --> 01:29.131
Who is she?

01:29.131 --> 01:32.426
She's my sister, Marisol.

01:32.426 --> 01:35.429
♪ dramatic music ♪

01:35.429 --> 01:40.434
♪♪♪

01:42.186 --> 01:46.273
♪ soft guitar music ♪

01:46.273 --> 01:49.276
[man and woman
moaning and grunting]

01:49.276 --> 01:53.697
♪♪♪

01:53.697 --> 01:55.533
[Marisol] I'm coming.

02:08.212 --> 02:11.507
[both breathing heavily]

02:11.507 --> 02:13.300
Oh, yeah.

02:13.300 --> 02:18.347
♪♪♪

02:26.021 --> 02:29.316
Anything on the DA?

02:29.316 --> 02:32.486
He clips his toenails,
he brushes his teeth,

02:32.486 --> 02:34.154
and he feeds his fish,

02:34.154 --> 02:35.948
but I'm sure tonight
is when a group of hookers

02:35.948 --> 02:37.533
are gonna show up
with a bottle of scotch

02:37.533 --> 02:39.785
and a shit-ton of Molly.

02:39.785 --> 02:42.580
Anything...

02:42.580 --> 02:44.373
from the DA?

02:44.373 --> 02:48.378
Well, no luck
with the evidence locker.

02:48.378 --> 02:51.171
Place has been shut down
since Muncie got killed.

02:54.049 --> 02:55.843
Oh, shit.

02:55.843 --> 02:58.304
I hope Ima's recording
So You Think You Can Dance.

02:59.389 --> 03:00.264
What?

03:00.264 --> 03:02.266
What? It's a great show.

03:02.266 --> 03:04.184
It has talented people.

03:04.184 --> 03:08.231
Look, Ray, there's no way
we're gonna turn this guy.

03:08.231 --> 03:09.898
We fucking can't,
and even if we could,

03:09.898 --> 03:12.192
he's not gonna
let Belikov out.

03:12.192 --> 03:14.486
She's right, boss.

03:14.486 --> 03:17.323
We should just fucking kill
Sonia Kovitsky.

03:19.409 --> 03:21.869
Keep watching him.

03:21.869 --> 03:22.870
[Avi]
But we--

03:27.250 --> 03:30.253
♪ solemn music ♪

03:30.253 --> 03:33.256
[door clicks open]

03:36.259 --> 03:37.176
[door slams]

03:37.176 --> 03:42.181
♪♪♪

03:48.771 --> 03:51.399
[sighs]

03:51.399 --> 03:54.818
We got to pull
the floors up, Ray.

03:54.818 --> 03:57.446
Yeah, we have
to replace them, Ray.

03:57.446 --> 04:00.407
[sighs]

04:05.871 --> 04:10.876
♪♪♪

04:17.424 --> 04:19.677
You sure you don't want
to get treatment?

04:22.221 --> 04:25.182
Why not?

04:25.182 --> 04:28.060
'Cause I don't have cancer.

04:28.060 --> 04:30.062
There's nothing there.

04:32.440 --> 04:36.527
It's just a test
some fucking asshole made up

04:36.527 --> 04:38.445
to make money,

04:38.445 --> 04:42.324
and it shows
every goddamn thing.

04:42.324 --> 04:44.493
It's stage zero.

04:50.541 --> 04:53.419
This isn't like your mom.

04:54.878 --> 04:56.839
This is different.

05:00.385 --> 05:02.094
Yeah.

05:05.806 --> 05:07.641
Are you okay?

05:10.936 --> 05:12.938
[chuckles softly]

05:16.275 --> 05:21.280
♪♪♪

05:27.495 --> 05:29.497
Go to bed.

05:31.165 --> 05:32.458
Good night.

05:34.168 --> 05:39.214
♪♪♪

06:19.379 --> 06:21.591
So...

06:21.591 --> 06:23.592
I've been speaking
to Jackson Holt,

06:23.592 --> 06:26.386
and he doesn't think
that Belikov

06:26.386 --> 06:28.472
killed those Armenians.

06:30.140 --> 06:33.769
Might be easier
if you told the truth.

06:33.769 --> 06:35.979
Turn yourself in
for the murders.

06:40.317 --> 06:42.361
[engine turns over]

06:50.953 --> 06:53.080
Hey, let's go.

06:53.080 --> 06:54.665
Come on.

07:21.358 --> 07:22.818
[clears throat]

07:27.865 --> 07:30.242
Leaving so soon,
Mr. Donovan?

07:33.203 --> 07:36.206
I'm going to meet
my new granddaughter.

07:36.206 --> 07:38.041
Oh, good heavens.

07:38.041 --> 07:41.378
Well, I hope
she's got your eyes.

07:41.378 --> 07:43.964
You look just like
Paul Newman.

07:43.964 --> 07:45.841
Thank you.

07:45.841 --> 07:47.467
Where is your granddaughter?

07:47.467 --> 07:49.344
Los Angeles.

07:49.344 --> 07:53.849
Well, I'm going as far
as the outlet malls in Covina,

07:53.849 --> 07:57.352
but maybe I can take you
all the way.

07:57.352 --> 07:59.938
- Sure. Great.
- Good.

07:59.938 --> 08:01.940
Right there.
Come on.

08:11.533 --> 08:13.869
Jesus Christ.

08:13.869 --> 08:16.538
Come on,
we're in a fucking drought.

08:20.000 --> 08:21.627
Homemade.

08:24.129 --> 08:27.799
[cell phone ringing]

08:27.799 --> 08:28.842
What?

08:28.842 --> 08:29.676
[Ray] Anything?

08:29.676 --> 08:31.637
[Avi] Nope.

08:31.637 --> 08:36.642
Dude just literally washed
his tuchus in a bidet.

08:36.642 --> 08:38.644
But we'll keep watching him.

08:38.644 --> 08:40.354
All right.

08:40.354 --> 08:41.647
[hip-hop music playing
on stereo]

08:41.647 --> 08:43.231
I can't wait
to smell her.

08:43.231 --> 08:44.858
I love the smell
of new babies.

08:44.858 --> 08:46.109
It brings back memories.

08:46.109 --> 08:47.861
What, shitty diapers
and no sleep?

08:47.861 --> 08:49.613
Yeah, like you'd
fucking know.

08:49.613 --> 08:51.490
Good. You're here.

08:51.490 --> 08:54.076
- What's so important, Bunch?
- Hey, Teresa.

08:54.076 --> 08:57.079
Come out here, will you?

08:57.079 --> 08:59.665
Oh, she looks
just like you, Bunch.

09:01.541 --> 09:03.543
[laughing]
Oh!

09:03.543 --> 09:05.253
Look at her.
Yeah.

09:05.253 --> 09:06.421
"Hi, Uncle Ray."

09:06.421 --> 09:07.839
[Abby]
Oh!

09:07.839 --> 09:10.760
[sighs]
Ray?

09:10.760 --> 09:12.427
What?

09:12.427 --> 09:14.596
I want you to be
the godfather to baby Maria.

09:23.605 --> 09:24.648
Bunch.

09:24.648 --> 09:26.233
[Maria coos]

09:29.569 --> 09:30.570
[Bunchy]
Lookit, I mean...

09:31.947 --> 09:33.741
I mean, God forbid

09:33.741 --> 09:36.702
something happened
to me and Teresa.

09:36.702 --> 09:38.203
Nothing's gonna happen.

09:38.203 --> 09:40.747
Yeah, I could get hit
by a bus.

09:40.747 --> 09:43.375
Teresa could get cancer.
You know.

09:47.713 --> 09:50.924
It's a real honor,
Bunchy, Teresa.

09:50.924 --> 09:52.635
Right, Ray?

09:52.635 --> 09:53.719
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

09:53.719 --> 09:54.720
Yeah.

09:54.720 --> 09:56.555
Well, you got to be
the godmother too.

09:58.098 --> 10:00.643
Oh.

10:00.643 --> 10:04.396
Yeah, Ray, congratulations.

10:04.396 --> 10:06.565
[Maria coos]

10:08.693 --> 10:11.278
[Daryll] Yeah, that, uh--
that's a good look, Ray.

10:11.278 --> 10:14.281
[hip-hop music continues]

10:14.281 --> 10:18.285
♪♪♪

10:19.704 --> 10:21.830
- [Maria coos]
- Aw.

10:23.957 --> 10:26.585
Did you know
that Paul Newman

10:26.585 --> 10:31.006
and Joanne Woodward
were married for 50 years?

10:31.006 --> 10:33.467
Till the day he died.

10:33.467 --> 10:37.220
Imagine.
In Hollywood. Huh.

10:37.220 --> 10:38.681
Why go out for hamburger

10:38.681 --> 10:40.098
when you got steak
at home to fuck?

10:40.098 --> 10:41.224
- [gasps]
- Right?

10:41.224 --> 10:42.476
Exactly.

10:42.476 --> 10:44.311
[both chuckle]

10:46.646 --> 10:50.693
♪ I don't care if it rains
or freezes ♪

10:50.693 --> 10:54.946
♪ As long as I have
my plastic Jesus ♪

10:54.946 --> 10:59.701
♪ Sittin' on the dashboard
of my car ♪

10:59.701 --> 11:03.789
♪ Comes in colors
pink and pleasant ♪

11:03.789 --> 11:08.668
♪ Glows in the dark
'cause it's iridescent ♪

11:08.668 --> 11:13.548
♪ Take it with you
when you travel far ♪

11:13.548 --> 11:15.884
♪ Oh, oh, oh, oh, oh ♪

11:15.884 --> 11:18.095
[cell phone ringing]

11:18.095 --> 11:19.764
Give me some
good news, Harriet.

11:19.764 --> 11:20.931
[Harriet]
There's no way

11:20.931 --> 11:22.724
I can get you
that money by tonight.

11:22.724 --> 11:24.351
That's refinancing
your apartment,

11:24.351 --> 11:25.894
selling the Fite Club.

11:25.894 --> 11:27.897
How fast can you do it?

11:27.897 --> 11:29.856
[Harriet]
Could take months, Ray.

11:29.856 --> 11:31.274
Get it done.

11:31.274 --> 11:33.693
[phone beeps, line rings]

11:33.693 --> 11:35.529
[cell phone buzzes]

11:37.489 --> 11:39.032
[Ray] Hey.

11:39.032 --> 11:40.826
Yeah, things are about
to get very interesting.

11:40.826 --> 11:42.327
He bought a labeling gun.

11:42.327 --> 11:43.829
[Ray] I'll take care of Holt.

11:43.829 --> 11:45.831
I need you to do something else.

11:45.831 --> 11:48.500
Really? Ray, I prom--
I'll do anything.

11:48.500 --> 11:49.543
Anything. I promise.

12:07.894 --> 12:09.896
[doorbell rings]

12:15.777 --> 12:18.989
Ray? Is everything okay?

12:18.989 --> 12:21.283
Everything's fine.

12:21.283 --> 12:24.161
- Can I come in?
- Of course.

12:24.161 --> 12:27.164
♪ somber music ♪

12:27.164 --> 12:32.169
♪♪♪

12:40.969 --> 12:42.762
Oh, Ray.

12:42.762 --> 12:45.015
I shouldn't have blown up
at you at the funeral.

12:45.015 --> 12:46.558
I'm so sorry.

12:46.558 --> 12:49.686
Don't worry about it.
I deserved it.

12:49.686 --> 12:52.772
I've missed you guys.

12:52.772 --> 12:56.818
Deb, I need to get
into Ezra's closet.

12:58.987 --> 13:00.947
[sighs]

13:02.866 --> 13:05.828
Nothing ever changes with you,
does it, Ray?

13:05.828 --> 13:08.914
I need to get into the safe.

13:08.914 --> 13:11.541
What fucking safe?

13:27.349 --> 13:30.685
♪ dramatic music ♪

13:30.685 --> 13:34.982
The two of you
and your fucking secrets.

13:34.982 --> 13:39.987
♪♪♪

13:56.503 --> 13:57.963
You're beautiful.

13:57.963 --> 13:59.339
Yeah?

13:59.339 --> 14:00.131
[clicking tongue]

14:00.131 --> 14:01.258
Yeah.

14:02.885 --> 14:05.136
- Where's Teresa?
- She's sleeping.

14:05.136 --> 14:07.681
I told her
I could look after Maria.

14:13.061 --> 14:15.146
It's a stupid
fucking tradition, Terry.

14:15.146 --> 14:16.439
Yeah.

14:16.439 --> 14:18.149
I know Ray was there
for you, Bunch,

14:18.149 --> 14:19.859
but I raised you too.

14:23.863 --> 14:25.282
I shouldn't have
brought it up.

14:25.282 --> 14:27.284
No, I get it.

14:27.284 --> 14:30.078
I don't have a wife.
I ain't got kids.

14:30.078 --> 14:32.414
I got fucking Parkinson's.

14:35.333 --> 14:37.502
I could ask Ray if maybe
he'd do it with you.

14:37.502 --> 14:39.087
Nah.

14:39.087 --> 14:42.257
I can't take care
of a fucking kid.

14:45.677 --> 14:47.345
[sighs]

14:52.851 --> 14:55.145
[doorbell rings]

14:55.145 --> 14:57.272
- [Lena] Hey, Abby.
- Lena?

14:57.272 --> 15:00.358
This is my friend Jeannie.

15:00.358 --> 15:02.402
- Hi.
- Hello.

15:02.402 --> 15:03.653
Ray asked me
to bring her over.

15:03.653 --> 15:05.196
She's a cancer doctor.

15:09.326 --> 15:12.203
Just fuck off,
both of you.

15:15.915 --> 15:18.918
[cell phone ringing]

15:20.420 --> 15:21.755
Hey.

15:21.755 --> 15:23.089
Are you gonna tell
the whole fucking world?

15:23.089 --> 15:24.549
Abs.

15:24.549 --> 15:28.136
[Abby] This is my
fucking problem, okay?

15:32.349 --> 15:34.142
What the fuck are you doing?

15:36.519 --> 15:38.271
Drinking.

15:38.271 --> 15:41.274
♪ dramatic music ♪

15:41.274 --> 15:46.279
♪♪♪

15:48.073 --> 15:51.951
[doorbell rings]

15:51.951 --> 15:54.954
Ray Donovan,
here to see Mr. Price.

15:58.416 --> 16:02.087
[Ronnie sobbing]

16:02.087 --> 16:03.713
[Ronnie] I knew.

16:03.713 --> 16:05.757
I fucking knew.

16:05.757 --> 16:08.009
She hated me.

16:08.009 --> 16:11.554
She fucking hated me,
and she wanted him.

16:11.554 --> 16:13.140
Something snapped.

16:13.140 --> 16:15.558
I hit her with that rope hook,

16:15.558 --> 16:17.811
and she fell into the water.

16:17.811 --> 16:21.898
I stood there,
and I let her drown.

16:21.898 --> 16:25.735
[Ezra] I need you to focus
on what I'm saying.

16:25.735 --> 16:27.612
Suzi had been drinking.

16:27.612 --> 16:30.907
You both went below deck
at 11 p.m.

16:30.907 --> 16:33.118
You went to sleep,
and when you woke up

16:33.118 --> 16:35.412
in the morning,
she was gone.

16:35.412 --> 16:37.164
[Ronnie] Ezra--

16:37.164 --> 16:40.208
[Ezra] Say it back to me.

16:40.208 --> 16:42.127
[Ronnie] Suzi had been drinking.

16:42.127 --> 16:46.090
We both went below deck
at 11 p.m.

16:46.090 --> 16:51.095
♪♪♪

16:54.055 --> 16:56.225
Ezra Goldman.

17:00.061 --> 17:01.980
So you blackmailing me?

17:04.065 --> 17:06.609
There's a Russian
named Ivan Belikov

17:06.609 --> 17:09.238
who's been charged
with killing eight Armenians.

17:09.238 --> 17:10.989
And?

17:10.989 --> 17:13.575
Jackson Holt
is prosecuting the case.

17:13.575 --> 17:15.535
Is this about money?

17:15.535 --> 17:18.037
I'll pay you more
than you're getting.

17:20.748 --> 17:23.460
Holt needs to drop
the charges.

17:25.128 --> 17:30.133
♪♪♪

17:35.222 --> 17:36.556
What's the worst thing
you ever did

17:36.556 --> 17:38.683
in your life,
Mr. Donovan?

17:41.228 --> 17:43.771
What wakes you up
in the middle of the night?

17:45.773 --> 17:47.692
How would you feel
if I came into your home

17:47.692 --> 17:52.071
and threw that horrible secret
in your face?

17:55.200 --> 17:57.286
It's not about me.

18:00.289 --> 18:04.209
Ezra promised me
this would go away.

18:04.209 --> 18:07.337
Told me it'd never come back.

18:07.337 --> 18:09.547
Ezra's dead.

18:09.547 --> 18:14.552
♪♪♪

18:25.855 --> 18:28.858
[cell phone ringing]

18:31.027 --> 18:32.403
Hector?

18:34.113 --> 18:35.073
I'll be right there.

18:47.293 --> 18:48.962
[sighs]

18:52.257 --> 18:54.176
Got to go to the bathroom,
sweetheart?

18:54.176 --> 18:55.468
No.

18:58.596 --> 19:00.306
Just resting
your eyes, huh?

19:00.306 --> 19:02.892
Uh-uh.

19:02.892 --> 19:05.186
You want me to drive
for a while?

19:05.186 --> 19:06.396
[sighs]

19:06.396 --> 19:09.399
[seat whirring]

19:17.824 --> 19:19.534
Need a nap, honey?

19:20.660 --> 19:22.954
Last thing on my mind.

19:22.954 --> 19:24.497
[chuckles]

19:26.249 --> 19:28.710
I was thinking

19:28.710 --> 19:33.340
today is not a good day
to go to the outlets.

19:33.340 --> 19:35.342
- No?
- No.

19:35.342 --> 19:37.677
And I was thinking

19:37.677 --> 19:42.557
a drive to LA
could be so nice.

19:42.557 --> 19:45.310
Well, thank you.

19:45.310 --> 19:47.687
It would be very kind of you.

19:47.687 --> 19:50.273
Mm-hmm.

19:50.273 --> 19:53.276
[humming]

20:16.341 --> 20:20.094
It ain't gonna
lick itself, Mickey.

20:31.189 --> 20:33.691
[Mickey]
Let the good times roll.

20:35.985 --> 20:38.363
- Why did you leave me?
- What's he on?

20:38.363 --> 20:40.281
He's dead.
He's fucking dead.

20:40.281 --> 20:41.324
What'd he fucking take?

20:41.324 --> 20:43.910
I don't know.
[sobbing]

20:46.288 --> 20:47.331
Shit.

20:47.331 --> 20:50.166
We were drinking.

20:50.166 --> 20:52.293
Fucking smoking.

20:52.293 --> 20:54.338
[sobbing]

20:54.338 --> 20:55.755
Fuck me!

20:55.755 --> 20:57.507
Don't let him die.

20:59.175 --> 21:00.635
- [retching]
- All right.

21:00.635 --> 21:02.261
All right.

21:02.261 --> 21:05.264
[Hector groaning]

21:09.894 --> 21:12.271
Oh, my God.

21:12.271 --> 21:14.732
- Thank you.
- [gasping]

21:14.732 --> 21:17.735
- Thank you.
- [coughing]

21:25.159 --> 21:27.120
So what's the deal
with you two?

21:27.120 --> 21:28.538
We're not together.

21:28.538 --> 21:30.499
That's not what I asked.

21:31.874 --> 21:34.544
We were together.

21:36.295 --> 21:37.880
Who broke up with who?

21:39.383 --> 21:40.466
She did.

21:40.466 --> 21:44.595
So this is your
guilt trip, huh?

21:44.595 --> 21:46.139
The fuck?

21:49.350 --> 21:51.561
Listen,

21:51.561 --> 21:55.022
I know a lot
about DCIS.

21:55.022 --> 21:56.816
I'm here to help.

22:05.450 --> 22:07.827
Listen, we haven't
figured it all out yet.

22:19.338 --> 22:21.174
We got bloodstains
on the floor.

22:21.174 --> 22:22.175
Hey, Abby.

22:22.175 --> 22:24.302
[clears throat]
Abby?

22:24.302 --> 22:27.180
You want to go do something?

22:27.180 --> 22:28.347
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

22:28.347 --> 22:30.183
Well, let's go, then.
Come on.

22:32.727 --> 22:34.521
